      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Gonna address a few things here, that I think I've posted elsewhere on this forum too.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The elves were created by Tunare and came to be known as Elddar elves for the forest in which they lived.&amp;nbsp; When they later fled Tunaria for greener pastures, primarly&amp;nbsp;Faydwer, the eventually evolved.&amp;nbsp; Someone mentioned that the Koada`Dal and Feir`Dal were more like classes, and I suppose you could look at it that way.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The nature-bound elves spent most of the time in the forests, etc. like the druids, rangers, and so on.&amp;nbsp;The&amp;nbsp;other elves, the politicians, paladins, clerics, and&amp;nbsp;those most tied to structure, tended to&amp;nbsp;congregate&amp;nbsp;indoors, for lack of a better description.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;You can consider that an evolution took place.&amp;nbsp; There would certainly have been remaining&amp;nbsp;Elddar while the Koada`Dal and Feir`Dal began to change and identify themselves differently.&amp;nbsp; Their bodies adapted to their environments, etc.&amp;nbsp; Then, eventually, the Elddar&amp;nbsp;as a race of elf vanished.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;As for the werewolves, their origins are described in the Depths of Darkhollow manual.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Vahlar&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
